      /* ---- about page ---- */
      about_why_h2: 'Why Is Reorganization Needed Now?<small>Why Now?</small>',
      issue1_h: 'Issue 1: Rapid Decline in Children',
      issue1_p: 'As of 2025, the population aged 19 and under in the Shinooka area has fallen to <strong>less than half compared to 20 years ago</strong>. Meanwhile, the population aged 65 and over has <strong>increased approximately 2.5 times</strong>.',
      issue2_h: 'Issue 2: Aging Facilities',
      issue2_p: 'Shinooka Elementary School was built in <strong>1958 (over 60 years ago)</strong>, and Shinooka Junior High School was built in <strong>1965 (about 60 years ago)</strong>. Other schools are similarly aging.',
      issue3_h: 'Issue 3: Shift to Single-Class Grades',
      issue3_p: 'If current trends continue, <strong>by 2033, all elementary schools and Shinooka Junior High School in the Shinooka area are projected to have only one class per grade</strong>.',
      stat_over_20y: 'over 20 years',
      stat_youth_label: 'Change in population under 19',
      stat_senior_label: 'Change in population over 65',
      stat_class_label: 'All elementary schools &amp; Shinooka JHS projected<br>to have 1 class per grade',
      stat_reorg_label: 'Phase 1 Reorganization (Planned)',
      about_city_view: '<strong>City\'s Position:</strong> "Given the declining number of students, there is no time to delay school reorganization — it must be carried out as soon as possible." (Komaki City Board of Education)',
      about_plan_h2: 'Phase 1 Reorganization Plan<small>Phase 1 Reorganization Plan</small>',
      about_plan_intro: 'In FY2027, the current <strong>5 elementary schools and 3 junior high schools</strong> will be reorganized into <strong>2 elementary schools and 2 junior high schools</strong>. Schools are grouped into "East" (Tokadai Higashi) and "West" (Tokadai Nishi).',
      about_elem_h3: '■ Elementary School Reorganization',
      about_jhs_h3: '■ Junior High School Reorganization',
      th_new_name: 'New School Name',
      th_merged: 'Schools to be Merged',
      th_note: 'Notes',
      about_oshiro_box: '<strong>About the Oshiro Elementary School District:</strong> The Oshiro district is divided into two. The Okusa/Shiroyama 3-chome area will merge into Tokadai Higashi Elementary, while the Shiroyama 2nd, 4th &amp; 5th-chome area will merge into Tokadai Nishi Elementary. For Shiroyama 3rd &amp; 4th-chome, a community meeting was held on July 27, 2025, and a resident survey was conducted before finalizing the district boundaries.',
      about_diagram_h3: '■ Reorganization Diagram',
      group_east: 'East Group',
      group_west: 'West Group',
      about_schools_h2: 'School Locations<small>School Locations</small>',
      about_mapnote_p: 'The map below shows the Shinooka area. Click each school name to view its location on Google Maps.',
      about_map_before_h4: '📚 Current Schools (Before Reorganization)',
      about_map_after_h4: '🏫 New Schools (from FY2027)',
      about_map_note: '※ The 4 new schools will use the existing buildings of the same-named schools.',
      about_commute_h2: 'Commuting Plan<small>Commuting Plan</small>',
      transport_elem_h: 'Elementary Students: School Bus',
      transport_elem_p: 'A <strong>school bus service is being introduced</strong> for elementary students.<br><br>· <strong>Morning route:</strong> 1 trip<br>· <strong>Afternoon routes:</strong> Up to 3 trips (on days with club activities)<br>· <strong>Cost: Fully covered by the city (free for students)</strong><br><br>Bus stops and schedules will be determined after coordination with schools and operators.',
      transport_jhs_h: 'Junior High Students: Bicycle Commuting',
      transport_jhs_p: '<strong>Bicycle commuting</strong> is planned for junior high students.<br><br>Details regarding safe commuting routes and rainy-day arrangements will be studied and announced at a later date.',
      about_phase2_h2: 'About Phase 2 Reorganization<small>Phase 2 (Future)</small>',
      about_phase2_box: '<strong>Outlook after Phase 1:</strong> If student numbers continue to decline after Phase 1 (FY2027), further consolidation into <strong>1 elementary and 1 junior high school</strong> may be considered, along with the introduction of <strong>integrated elementary-junior high education</strong>. The decision on Phase 2 will be made based on the situation following Phase 1.',
      about_buildings_h2: 'About Closed School Facilities<small>Closed School Buildings</small>',
      building_h: 'School Buildings',
      building_p: 'The buildings of closed schools are <strong>generally planned to be demolished</strong>.',
      gym_h: 'Gymnasium &amp; School Grounds',
      gym_p: 'Gymnasiums and school grounds are <strong>generally planned to be kept</strong>. They are expected to be used for local sports and community activities.',
      about_process_h2: 'Decision-Making Process<small>Decision-Making Process</small>',
      about_contact_h2: 'Contact the City<small>Contact</small>',
      /* ---- map page ---- */
      map_overview_h2: 'Area Overview Map<small>Area Overview</small>',
      map_overview_p: 'An overview of the Shinooka area (around Tokadai). Click the school name links to view details on Google Maps.',
      map_h4_new4: '🏫 4 New Schools (from FY2027)',
      map_before_h2: 'Current School Locations<small>Current School Locations</small>',
